UIScreens

UIScreens is a project designed for developers looking to hone their skills in creating user interfaces programmatically using UIKit. This repository serves as a playground for practicing the art of building elegant and responsive UIs without relying on Interface Builder or storyboards.

Features

Programmatic UI Creation: Learn the ins and outs of building user interfaces from scratch using UIKit components.
Modular Design: Explore various UI elements organized into separate modules, making it easy to focus on specific components.
Responsive Layouts: Practice creating layouts that adapt gracefully to different screen sizes and orientations.
Interactive Examples: Dive into interactive examples that demonstrate how to handle user input, animations, and transitions programmatically.
UIKit Best Practices: Follow best practices and design patterns while constructing your UI elements for maintainability and scalability.
